Leave is the default option while Boris Johnson is still PM. Recent strategies of prorogation and talk of a legal challenge to the Benn Bill, indicate that BJ is trying to hold the line until mid October. This forecast has been made considering the following points: 
Brexit is not a desirable outcome for the EU - I predict that the EU will offer an extension whether it is sought or not; 
Assuming BJ remains in power - if there is a vote of no confidence in Boris Johnson's government, this forecast would be drastically revised; 
The legal challenge to the prorogation of parliament is likely to fail;
A general election at this point in time would probably return Boris Johnson to power.
